    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hvidovre University Hospital</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to compare systematic local infiltration with ropivacaine or
      placebo in patients undergoing repair of posterior vaginal wall prolapse.

      The hypothesis is that LIA technique is opioid-sparing and a better postoperative treatment.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
